TI  - Regional funding and regional inequalities in the Brazilian Northeast
JO  - Regional Science Policy and Practice
PY  - 2020
VL  - 12
IS  - 1
SP  - 43-59
DO  - 10.1111/rsp3.12230
UR  - https://www.scopus.com/inward/record.uri?eid=2-s2.0-85071323524&doi=10.1111%2Frsp3.12230&partnerID=40&md5=eff77a7845c9342b427498ad86e3ff57
AB  - This paper investigates the impacts of a very important credit policy in Brazil called Northeast Financing Constitutional Fund (FNE in Portuguese) using a dynamic and inter-regional computable general equilibrium model calibrated for 2013. Simulations were carried out based on FNE investment data for 2014 and 2015, allowing for isolation of the effect of the funding on macro regions. Results indicate that FNE expenditures between 2014 and 2015 would increase Northeast GDP by 3.51% by 2025. Estimates show a 0.46% decrease in regional inequality among Northeastern states measured by regional GINI. Results are compatible with the objectives of the fund, although the total effects, mainly on regional inequality, are quite modest. © 2019 The Author(s). Regional Science Policy and Practice © 2019 RSAI
